The aim of the course is to give the student the possibility to be physically active to promote health. The chosen discipline is free to choose. The course is fully web-based. During the course the student has to collect training/workout related data and to record them into the chosen web software. The data can be entered manually or using different smart devices (preferred). Additionally, the summaries about the workouts must be compiled. In Moodle the learning materials must be analysed and a written test must be done related to the impact of physical load and physical activity to human body.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to acknowledge through practical movement (physical activity) the impact of physical exercises on human body and to analyse the workouts and self-condition using the appropriate softwareLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) Has been physically active at the minimal level that has health promoting effect; 2) Knows how to use the software in order to monitor and analyse the workouts; 3) Knows possibilities how to handle with limitations to be physically active.
